cs.LO, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.DB, cs.CG

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the expressive power of order-invariant monadic second-order (MSO) and first-order (FO) logic. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper studies the expressive power of order-invariant logic on restricted classes of structures. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is another possible category as the paper discusses the complexity classes captured by order-invariant formulas. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is relevant as the paper mentions the independence of the answer to a database query from low-level aspects of databases. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions planar graphs, which are often studied in computational geometry.
